Market Analysis and Size

Procurement as a service deals with the operational activities in a business such as managing and ensuring the supplies. It is a technological system that enhances employee visibility and MSP management to control the expenditure. Rising number of small and medium scale end users are increasingly understanding the importance of procurement as a service. Hewlett Packard Enterprise Development LP (US), HCL Technologies (India), Tata Consultancy Services Limited (India), Xchanging (UK), Aegis (India), Corbus (India), and CA Technologies (US) are the some major players operating in this market.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the procurement as a service market value, which was USD 6.21 billion in 2021, is expected to reach the value of USD 11.17 billion by 2029, at a CAGR of 7.60% during the forecast period. “Manufacturing" accounts for the largest vertical segment in the procurement as a service market owing to the growing rate of adoption of procurement as a service by small and medium scale enterprises. The procurement as a service market report also covers pricing analysis, patent analysis, and technological advancements in depth.

